    "created_at": "2017-03-10T21:33:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-03-10T21:33:02Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think this is technically interesting, but i'm not sold on it as a feature.\r\n\r\nRight now our explicit condition granting makes it easy for modders (who may not be programmers and very likely don't know the specific details of OpenRA's internals) to understand what is going on, and it also makes it very easy to statically lint condition usage.\r\n\r\nAdding an extra layer on top to implicitly construct granted condition types feels like a step backwards: it adds cognitive and code overhead, but doesn't seem to enable any new capabilities (except for removing boilerplate, but as above I consider the current level of boilerplate to be a feature).\r\n\r\nCan you please convince me otherwise?"
  },
