    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I'm a bit conflicted, because while I agree with @pchote on all the points,  if multiple Health traits would ever happen (and such were among the long-term developer wishlist, according to the discussion back at my damagetypes-without-warheads PR), then I guess that would justify the health setups (although probably by then we will have a method to differ between the multiple Health traits for selfhealing and etc as well which GrantConditionOnDamageState could use as well).\r\n\r\nGrantConditionWithSound isn't using explicit interfaces either which is a problem in design terms and a prime example why I never and still doesn't favor the reasons behind explicit interfaces here either."
  },
